            <li>Glute bridges: 3 sets of 10 reps</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Day 3: Wednesday (Core)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Plank: 3 sets of 30-second hold</li>
            <li>Russian twists (using a medicine ball): 3 sets of 10 reps</li>
            <li>Leg raises (hanging leg raises or using a swiss ball): 3 sets of 10 reps</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Day 4: Thursday (Cardio)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Jumping jacks: 3 sets of 30 seconds</li>
            <li>Running in place: 3 sets of 30 seconds</li>
            <li>Burpees: 3 sets of 10 reps</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Day 5: Friday (Yoga)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Downward-facing dog: 3 sets of 30-second hold</li>
            <li>Warrior II: 3 sets of 30-second hold (per leg)</li>
            <li>Seated forward fold: 3 sets of 30-second hold</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Day 6: Saturday (Pilates)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Hundred: 3 sets of 30-second hold</li>
            <li>Teaser: 3 sets of 10 reps</li>
            <li>Leg raises (using a Pilates ball): 3 sets of 10 reps</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Day 7: Sunday (Stretching)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Hamstring stretch: 3 sets of 30-second hold (per leg)</li>
            <li>Chest stretch: 3 sets of 30-second hold</li>
            <li>Quad stretch: 3 sets of 30-second hold (per leg)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
